From 244ab86618e36a5754a97ec3e254dcdf04006dbb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Thomas Wu <quic_wthomas@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 27 Feb 2025 14:21:53 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 137/141] wifi: ath12k: Disable broadcast TWT feature bit

Currently, the AP does not support the broadcast TWT feature.
Therefore, disable the broadcast TWT feature in the HE MAC element field.

Tested-on: QCN9274 hw2.0 PCI WLAN.WBE.1.3.1-00209-QCAHKSWPL_SILICONZ-1

Signed-off-by: Thomas Wu <quic_wthomas@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Aaradhana Sahu <quic_aarasahu@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Raj Kumar Bhagat <quic_rajkbhag@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Jeff Johnson <jeff.johnson@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
index 2c49c106c37f..e04b076e1bd5 100644
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mac.c
@@ -7488,6 +7488,7 @@ static void ath12k_mac_copy_he_cap(struct ath12k *ar,
 
 	switch (iftype) {
 	case NL80211_IFTYPE_AP:
+		he_cap_elem->mac_cap_info[2] &= ~IEEE80211_HE_MAC_CAP2_BCAST_TWT;
 		he_cap_elem->phy_cap_info[3] &=
 			~IEEE80211_HE_PHY_CAP3_DCM_MAX_CONST_TX_MASK;
 		he_cap_elem->phy_cap_info[9] |=
-- 
